Bola Bamigbola, Osogbo A 52-year-old woman, Adijat Lukuman, on Thursday, appeared before an Osun State Magistratesâ€™ Court sitting in Osogbo for stealing earrings worth N40,000. The defendant admitted stealing the items and was remanded in police custody by the court. The police prosecutor, Rasaq Olayiwola, said the defendant committed the offence on January 13, 2020, at the Ilesha Garage area of Osogbo. He added that the defendant stole the earrings from one Titilayo Adekunle. According to him, the offences are contrary to and punishable under sections 390 and 249, Cap 34 Vol. ll, Law of Osun State, 2002. The defendant pleaded guilty to the two counts preferred against her. Counsel for the defendant, Ibrahim Imran, pleaded for leniency of the court. In her ruling, the magistrate, Risikat Olayemi, remanded the defendant in police custody. She subsequently adjourned the matter till January 30, 2020. Copyright PUNCH.
